{
    "chapterId": "how-was-it-made",
    "title": "How was it made?",
    "pages": [
        {
            "pageId": 10,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "Make-zStack-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "To visualize and quantify specific structures in hiPS cells, we endogenously tag protein components of those structures with <span style=\"color:#ffffff\">fluorescent proteins (FPs)</span> via gene editing.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 11,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "Make-zStack-2",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This allows structures such as <span style=\"color:#00ff00\">microtubules</span> to stand out from the other components of the cells.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "media",
                        "mediaId": "Microtubule-aTubulin-VE",
                        "element": "",
                        "caption": "<span style=\"color:white\">Microtubules</span> comprised of <span style=\"color:white\">tubulin dimers</span> with ⍺-tubulin tagged by an endogenously attached fluorescent protein, <span style=\"color:#00ff00\"\">mEGFP</span>."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 12,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "Make-zStack-3",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We use confocal microscopy to image whole, living cells as 3D volumes.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "media",
                        "mediaId": "Microtubule-ONLY-wholecell",
                        "element": "",
                        "caption": "Illustrated cross section of a single hiPS cell living in an epithelial sheet with organelles drawn approximately to scale and <span style=\"color:#00ff00\"\">microtubules</span> highlighted in green. The illustration animates to simulate the resolution of a spinning disk confocal microscope to explain why microtubules look more like a “blobby web” of tall tubes ~300nm in diameter instead of distinct fibers that are known to be ~25nm in diameter."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 13,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "Make-zStack-4",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We label the cell membrane and <span class=\"dna\">DNA</span> with fluorescent dyes to give a frame of reference for the <span style=\"color:#00ff00\">FP-tagged structures</span>, in this case, <span style=\"color:#00ff00\"\">microtubules</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "The boundaries of each fluorescent label are identified via segmentation. The cell membrane boundary permits us to isolate any cell to visualize and quantify its structures.",
                        "element": "p"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 14,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This cell is part of our database...",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 15,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-1-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "fade",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This cell is part of our database, which contains tens of thousands of segmented cell images.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 16,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-2",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "In addition to <span class=\"microtubules\">microtubules</span>, we have labeled many other intracellular structures and organelles, such as <span class=\"mitochondria\">mitochondria</span>, <span class=\"golgi\">Golgi</span>, <span class=\"actin-filaments\">actin</span>, and <span class=\"nucleolus\">nucleoli</span>. <span style=\"color:#b7b7b700\">We artificially color-code each structure in this presentation to help them stand apart.</span>",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 17,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-2-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "fade",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "In addition to <span class=\"microtubules\">microtubules</span>, we have labeled many other intracellular structures and organelles, such as <span class=\"mitochondria\">mitochondria</span>, <span class=\"golgi\">Golgi</span>, <span class=\"actin-filaments\">actin</span>, and <span class=\"nucleolus\">nucleoli</span>. We artificially color-code each structure in this presentation to help them stand apart.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 18,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-3",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Each image is a snapshot in time, creating a vast database of living cells captured in various stages of the cell cycle.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 19,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-4",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can scan through cells in this database to sort them into one of five categories based on the shape and texture patterns of their <span class=\"dna\">DNA</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 20,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-4-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can scan through cells in this database to sort them into one of five categories based on the shape and texture patterns of their <span class=\"dna\">DNA</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 21,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-5",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "To create the Integrated Mitotic Stem Cell model we picked similarly shaped representative cells for each structure within a given stage.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 22,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "DeepZoom-6",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This procedure constructs a grid with 15 cellular structures across 5 stages.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 23,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "Orient-key-cell-1",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "An algorithm aligned each cell to appear to divide horizontal to this page based on <span class=\"dna\">DNA</span> and cell morphology. For example, we rotated the metaphase tubulin cell such that its <span class=\"dna\">DNA</span>, the metaphase plate, was oriented vertically. Sometimes we fine-tuned the alignment manually.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 24,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
